L. Rogers Lytton https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/L._Rogers_Lytton 0 L. Rogers Lytton (April 9, 1867 – August 9, 1924) was an American film actor of the silent era. He appeared in more than 90 films between 1912 and 1924. Prior to entering films he had a substantial stage career behind him. He was born in New Orleans, Louisiana, and died in New York, New York.
